{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Js7f6uKjGeUWTjrzMri2Dk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The TLS certificate's SANs are:\n- `DNS:localhost`\n- `DNS:*.elasticsearch.svc`\n- `DNS:*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n\nThis covers:\n- HTTP access via `es-http.elasticsearch.svc` and `es-http.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n- The wildcard `*.elasticsearch.svc` also covers the headless service `es-headless.elasticsearch.svc`\n\nBut for transport (pod-to-pod communication), the addresses would be like:\n- `es-0.es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n- `es-1.es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n- `es-2.es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n\nThe wildcard `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` only matches one level deep, so it covers `es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` but not the pod-specific names like `es-0.es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`. This means the certificate doesn't actually cover the pod DNS names used for transport communication, so I need to find another approach.\n\nWhen discovery uses `es-headless`, Elasticsearch resolves it to the pod IPs directly, which means I should verify whether the certificate validation is even necessary for transport or if I can rely on IP-based communication instead.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1737,"cache_read_input_tokens":37254,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1737},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c0b1296-0e9b-43ed-93fa-923757142c60","uuid":"b76bed78-5670-49d1-891f-0368cf977db6","request_id":"req_011CcLcSqyrWos35CL4Njq7p"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Js7f6uKjGeUWTjrzMri2Dk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cert's SANs cover `*.elasticsearch.svc` and `*.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` — good for HTTP. For transport (pod-to-pod on 9300), pod names like `es-0.es-headless.*` don't match, so I'll use `verification_mode: certificate` for transport TLS to skip hostname checks.\n\nNow I'll create and apply the full deployment manifest."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1737,"cache_read_input_tokens":37254,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1737},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c0b1296-0e9b-43ed-93fa-923757142c60","uuid":"ddb766d8-ad03-4916-95fc-a50861f3ad4b","request_id":"req_011CcLcSqyrWos35CL4Njq7p"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Js7f6uKjGeUWTjrzMri2Dk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KxSKVdiKLJzc8dPvgHP3rw","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/es-deploy.yaml","content":"---\n# Headless service for intra-cluster pod discovery\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: es-headless\n  namespace: elasticsearch\n  labels:\n    app: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  clusterIP: None\n  selector:\n    app: elasticsearch\n  ports:\n    - name: transport\n      port: 9300\n      targetPort: 9300\n    - name: https\n      port: 9200\n      targetPort: 9200\n---\n# ClusterIP service for HTTPS client access\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: es-http\n  namespace: elasticsearch\n  labels:\n    app: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  selector:\n    app: elasticsearch\n  ports:\n    - name: https\n      port: 9200\n      targetPort: 9200\n      protocol: TCP\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: es-config\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  elasticsearch.yml: |\n    cluster.name: es-cluster\n    node.name: ${HOSTNAME}\n    network.host: 0.0.0.0\n\n    discovery.seed_hosts: es-headless\n    cluster.initial_master_nodes: es-0,es-1,es-2\n\n    xpack.security.enabled: true\n\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate_authorities: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n\n    # Use cert from es-http-tls for transport too; skip hostname check since pod\n    # FQDNs (es-N.es-headless.*) aren't in the cert SANs, only *.elasticsearch.svc is.\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.verification_mode: certificate\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate_authorities: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n---\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: StatefulSet\nmetadata:\n  name: es\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  serviceName: es-headless\n  replicas: 3\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: elasticsearch\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: elasticsearch\n    spec:\n      initContainers:\n        - name: sysctl\n          image: busybox\n          command:\n            - sh\n            - -c\n            - sysctl -w vm.max_map_count=262144\n          securityContext:\n            privileged: true\n      containers:\n        - name: elasticsearch\n          image: docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1\n          env:\n            - name: ELASTIC_PASSWORD\n              valueFrom:\n                secretKeyRef:\n                  name: elastic-password\n                  key: password\n            - name: ES_JAVA_OPTS\n              value: \"-Xms512m -Xmx512m\"\n          ports:\n            - name: https\n              containerPort: 9200\n            - name: transport\n              containerPort: 9300\n          volumeMounts:\n            - name: config\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.yml\n              subPath: elasticsearch.yml\n            - name: certs\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs\n              readOnly: true\n            - name: data\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\n          readinessProbe:\n            exec:\n              command:\n                - sh\n                - -c\n                - |\n                  curl -sk -u \"elastic:${ELASTIC_PASSWORD}\" \\\n                    https://localhost:9200/_cluster/health \\\n                  | grep -qE '\"status\":\"(green|yellow)\"'\n            initialDelaySeconds: 60\n            periodSeconds: 10\n    